<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-17T15:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-27T14:00:00-05:00" n="292" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/166</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Advisory Commission of
                                    Railway Experts to Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJF1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1917-09-17T16:30:00-04:00" notBefore="1917-08-27T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        September 17, 1917, 4.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>[For] <persName corresp="#p_WD1">Willard</persName>:</p>
                            <p>Have heard nothing further from <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName> or you since your cables-August 17.
                                Commission to arrive Vladivostok September 28 and must then be
                                advised of situation and what you have decided as to our
                                recommendations upon which the movements of commission depend. There
                                is a decided improvement efficiency Siberian Railway already as a
                                result of our work and expect much greater results from our present
                                trip with government officials. Answer quickly, care Consul at
                                Vladivostok.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_SJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>